<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 4:52AM CDT  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...A thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Stephenson
County through 515 AM CDT...
At 452 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a thunderstorm 7 miles
north of Cedarville, or 8 miles south of Monroe, moving east at 55
mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Rock City around 500 AM CDT.
Davis around 505 AM CDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
